        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-07-05 08:10:18.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1598 osd: bypass OI lookup for creation",
        "message": "LU-1598 osd: bypass OI lookup for creation\n\nIt's unnecessary to call osd_oi_lookup() in osd_fid_lookup if it's a\nfile creation because FID shouldn't never be re-used so we expect it\nto be not existed, which means we can bypass overhead of OI lookup at\nhere, if it's really a duplicate FID from unexpected reasons, we\nshould detect it later while calling do_create->osd_oi_insert().\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I87227a4e7d008c06876b1366734832886868de3b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
